</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF8FFB9FC959F1F6D197EEF" blockId="21.[831,1437,802,967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">
1946. 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF8FFB9FC289F1F6DCF7E10" authority="(PLUMMER)" baseAuthorityName="PLUMMER" box="[898,1218,859,881]" class="Nodosariata" family="Vaginulinidae" genus="Marginulina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaginulinida" pageId="21" pageNumber="35" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="silicula">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FC289F1F6D447E11" box="[898,1097,859,880]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Marginulina silicula</emphasis>
(PLUMMER)
</taxonomicName>
.- CUSHMAN, p. 62, pl. 21, figs. 42-45.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF8FFB9FC959FD06ADF7EA6" blockId="21.[831,1437,802,967]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">
1985. 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF8FFB9FC289FD06DE87ECB" authority="(PLUMMER)" baseAuthorityName="PLUMMER" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[898,1253,916,938]" class="Nodosariata" family="Vaginulinidae" genus="Marginulinopsis" kingdom="Chromista" order="Vaginulinida" pageId="21" pageNumber="35" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="silicula">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FC289FD06D607EC8" box="[898,1133,916,937]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Marginulinopsis silicula</emphasis>
(PLUMMER)
</taxonomicName>
.- LUGER, p. 83, pl. 5, fig. 5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF8FFB9FC959FAF6D8279C2" blockId="21.[831,1437,1003,1187]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FC959FAF6D707962" bold="true" box="[831,1149,1003,1027]" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Paleocene of North America by CUSHMAN (1927) and in the Paleocene of Gebel Nekhl in 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFF8FFB9FB74986F6C187922" box="[1246,1301,1067,1091]" country="Egypt" name="Shamal Sina'" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Sinai</collectingRegion>
by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956). It is recorded in the Esna Shale of the Esh El Mallaha area 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FBB0982F6D2F79E2" box="[1050,1058,1131,1155]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">(</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF8FFB9FB8B982F6C7D79E3" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[1057,1392,1131,1155]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="21" pageNumber="35" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="velascoensis">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FB8B982F6C3E79E2" box="[1057,1331,1131,1155]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Morozovella velascoensis</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF8FFB9FC9598CF6D8E79C2" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[831,1155,1163,1187]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="21" pageNumber="35" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="subbotinae">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF8FFB9FC9598CF6D4C79C2" box="[831,1089,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="35">Morozovella subbotinae</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
